This travel advice also covers American Samoa, Guam, Northern Mariana Islands, Puerto Rico, and United States Virgin Islands.
The Foreign, Commonwealth & Development Office (FCDO) provides advice about risks of travel to help British nationals make informed decisions. Find out more about FCDO travel advice.
Vermont floods
There has been widespread flooding in Vermont in recent days, particularly concentrated in the Montpelier area.  Further rain is forecast.  Visitors and residents should monitor the weather forecast and follow advice and guidance from the local authorities, particularly around road closures, power outages and advice around what to do in the event of potential contamination of drinking water.
British Nationals in the area should follow:
the Vermont Emergency Management Department, also see Twitter updates
the Federal Emergency Management Agency Region One, also see Twitter updates
the National Weather Service in Burlington, Vermont also see Twitter updates
The British Consulate in Boston is routinely re-posting official guidance on its social media channels, mainly on its Twitter account.
Before you travel
No travel can be guaranteed safe. Read all the advice in this guide as well as support for British nationals abroad which includes:
advice on preparing for travel abroad and reducing risks
information for women, LGBT+ and disabled travellers
Follow and contact FCDO travel on Twitter, Facebook and Instagram. You can also sign up to get email notifications when this advice is updated.
Travel insurance
If you choose to travel, research your destinations and get appropriate travel insurance. Insurance should cover your itinerary, planned activities and expenses in an emergency.
